    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "Coral Gables, Fla. --\nDespite a three RBI day from shortstop\nBen North\n, Creighton Baseball fell at Miami 15-5 as the Bluejays were swept by the Hurricanes on Sunday, March 22. The loss moved Creighton to 9-11 on the season, while Miami climbed to 18-6.\nBluejay starter\nEli Nissen\ntook the loss (0-1), allowing three runs on three hits and two walks in two innings. Miami reliever TJ Coats earned the win (3-0), allowing one run on three hits in 1.2 innings.\nDown 3-0 after two frames, North brought Creighton within a run as he blasted an 0-1 pitch over the left field wall with two down in the inning.\nMiami answered with three consecutive solo home runs in the third by Alex Sosa, Derek Williams and Brylan West. The Hurricanes tacked one three more in the fourth to lead 9-2.\nCreighton rallied with three runs of its own in the fifth as\nRocco Gump\ndrew a one-out walk, then\nNate McHugh\nturned an 0-2 count into a hit by pitch. North followed with an RBI double to left. With two down in the frame\nIsaac Wachsmann\nlined a two-run double to left to bring Creighton back within striking distance at 9-5.\nThe Hurricane offense, however, refused to be denied. Miami scored one in the fifth, three in the sixth and two in the eighth to close out the game at 15-5.\nThere is no rest for the well traveled Bluejay squad as Creighton plays five games this week, all at Charles Schwab Field Omaha, beginning against Omaha on Tuesday, March 24 at 6:00 pm and then faces South Dakota State on Wednesday, March 25.",
